<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLBORDER="1" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="4">
  <TR><TD BGCOLOR="#b6e3b6" WIDTH="150"><B>Rule</B></TD></TR>
  <TR><TD ALIGN="left" WIDTH="150">Section 112 (i) provides, so far as<BR ALIGN='left'/>material:\n\n&quot;(1) The term<BR ALIGN='left'/>`reorganization&#x27; means (A) a merger or<BR ALIGN='left'/>consolidation (including the acquisition<BR ALIGN='left'/>by one corporation of at least a<BR ALIGN='left'/>majority of the voting stock and at<BR ALIGN='left'/>least a majority of the total number of<BR ALIGN='left'/>shares of all other 420*420 classes of<BR ALIGN='left'/>stock of another corporation, or<BR ALIGN='left'/>substantially all the properties of<BR ALIGN='left'/>another corporation) . . .&quot;</TD></TR>
